		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For an interactive disassembler, IDA is a good one.  It's a commercial program, but there's a version of it on the site here.  I don't know what limits there are in this free version (mostly CPU support I think, but this one supports 6502).
<br /><a href="http://nesdev.com/idafw.zip" class="postlink">http://nesdev.com/idafw.zip</a>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


