	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There are ancient 6502 simulators like p65 on Linux/Unix that should compile fairly easily on OSX. Text based, but you can do stuff like check the processor state and step through the operations which is useful for debugging loops and things.
<br />I've been thinking of writing one myself (I use OSX and Linux exclusively), but I haven't decided how I'd want it to work.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


